#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.h1:17-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\creating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm+html.body.h1:17-1"
msgid "Creating a Graphic Label Manually"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:18-1
msgid ""
"To practice creating a Graphic Label, use HJPad. To launch HJPad go to Start, "
"All Programs, JAWS <em>X</em> (where <em>X</em> is the JAWS version number), Run "
"HJPad."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:19-1
msgid ""
"Using the Graphics Labeler is easy, but before you start ensure that JAWS is set "
"to speak graphics. Follow these steps to be sure:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:21-1
msgid "With HJPad open, press <strong>INSERT+V</strong> to open Quick Settings."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:22-1
msgid ""
"In the Search box, type the term \"graphics\" (without the quotes), and then "
"press <strong>DOWN ARROW</strong> to move to the Graphics option in the tree "
"view."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:23-1
msgid "Press the <strong>SPACEBAR</strong> until you hear JAWS say, \"All.\""
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:24-1
msgid ""
"Next, press <strong>ENTER</strong> to accept the change, and then close Quick "
"Settings."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:26-1
msgid ""
"Now that all graphics will be spoken, you are ready to find a graphic to label."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:28-1
msgid "Press the <strong>NUM PAD MINUS</strong> key to activate the JAWS cursor."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:30-1
msgid ""
"<strong>Tip:</strong> To navigate to the toolbar, first press <strong>PAGE UP</"
"strong> to move to the top of the window, and then press <strong>HOME</strong> "
"to move to the top, left."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:32-1
msgid ""
"Use the <strong>ARROW Keys </strong>to move to the first toolbar button. You "
"will hear, \"Graphic XXX.\" XXX can indicate any number."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:33-1
msgid "Press <strong>INSERT+G</strong> to open the Graphics Labeler."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:34-1
msgid ""
"When the Graphics Labeler is opened, the focus is in the edit field, where you "
"should enter the label for the graphic. It will contain the graphic and the "
"number that is assigned to it. Type the name for your graphic."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:35-1
msgid ""
"Press the <strong>TAB</strong> key to move to the braille label field. Here you "
"can enter a label for a braille display."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:36-1
msgid ""
"Next press the <strong>TAB</strong> key to move to a group of radio buttons that "
"will let you determine where you want to save the label, in the application "
"file, default file, or both files."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:37-1
msgid "Press <strong>ENTER</strong> to activate your graphic label."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ccreating_a_graphic_label_manually.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:39-1
msgid ""
"<strong>Note:</strong> To edit a graphic label, use the same procedure that you "
"would to create a new graphic label, and just change the name of the label in "
"the Graphics Labeler when it opens. To delete a graphic label, do the same, but "
"delete the name in the Graphics Labeler."
msgstr ""

